    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n538" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ἀλήιον</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πεδίον</span>: the <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">Aleïan</span> plain, scene of
          Bellerophon's wandering, in Cilicia according to the later legend,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 6.201</span></i>†. The name seems to
          involve a play upon <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀλᾶτο</span> (in the same
          v.), cf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ἀλύβᾱς</span>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
